doc_string.value:
@dev Update mining rate and supply at the start of the epoch
         Any modifying mining call must also call this
@notice Current number of tokens in existence (claimed or unclaimed)
@notice Total number of tokens in existence.

msg.value: Only admin is allowed to change name

natspec.author: Mobius Finance
natspec.details: Based on the ERC-20 token standard as defined at https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-20

allowance(address,address).notice: Check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender

params._owner: The address which owns the funds
params._spender: The address which will spend the funds

returns._0: uint256 specifying the amount of tokens still available for the spender

approve(address,uint256).details: Approval may only be from zero -> nonzero or from nonzero -> zero in order to mitigate the potential race condition described here: https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/20#issuecomment-263524729
approve(address,uint256).notice: Approve `_spender` to transfer `_value` tokens on behalf of `msg.sender`

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds
params._value: The amount of tokens to be spent

available_supply().notice: Current number of tokens in existence (claimed or unclaimed)

burn(uint256).details: Emits a Transfer event with a destination of 0x00

params._value: The amount that will be burned

future_epoch_time_write().notice: Get timestamp of the next mining epoch start while simultaneously updating mining parameters

mint(address,uint256).details: Emits a Transfer event originating from 0x00
mint(address,uint256).notice: Mint `_value` tokens and assign them to `_to`

params._to: The account that will receive the created tokens
params._value: The amount that will be created

mintable_in_timeframe(uint256,uint256).notice: How much supply is mintable from start timestamp till end timestamp

set_admin(address).details: After all is set up, admin only can change the token name

set_minter(address).details: Only callable once, when minter has not yet been set

set_name(string,string).details: Only callable by the admin account
set_name(string,string).notice: Change the token name and symbol to `_name` and `_symbol`

start_epoch_time_write().notice: Get timestamp of the current mining epoch start while simultaneously updating mining parameters

totalSupply().notice: Total number of tokens in existence.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Vyper does not allow underflows, so the subtraction in this function will revert on an insufficient balance

params._from: address The address which you want to send tokens from
params._to: address The address which you want to transfer to
params._value: uint256 the amount of tokens to be transferred

update_mining_parameters().details: Callable by any address, but only once per epoch Total supply becomes slightly larger if this function is called late
update_mining_parameters().notice: Update mining rate and supply at the start of the epoch
